<def f='exim/src/tls-openssl.c' l='2852' ll='2926' type='int vaguely_random_number(int max)'/>
<doc f='exim/src/tls-openssl.c' l='2841'>/* Pseudo-random number generation.  The result is not expected to be
cryptographically strong but not so weak that someone will shoot themselves
in the foot using it as a nonce in input in some email header scheme or
whatever weirdness they&apos;ll twist this into.  The result should handle fork()
and avoid repeating sequences.  OpenSSL handles that for us.

Arguments:
  max       range maximum
Returns     a random number in range [0, max-1]
*/</doc>
